# Canonical line endings: LF in the working tree on every platform.
#
# The repo's blobs are already LF; without this, `core.autocrlf=true` checks them
# out as CRLF on Windows, which breaks byte-identity tests (e.g. bevy_elision's
# shrink->expand->shrink) on the Windows CI `test` job. Forcing eol=lf keeps the
# working tree LF everywhere so those tests pass cross-platform.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets must never be line-ending converted.
*.png binary
